<!DOCTYPE document SYSTEM "sonnet29.dtd">
<document>
	<sonnet>
		<title>Sonnet XXIX</title>
		<quatrain number="1">
			<line number="1">When in disgrace with fortune and men's e<rhyme scheme="A" type="perfect" cadence="antecedent">yes</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="2">I all alone beweep my outcast st<rhyme scheme="B" type="perfect" cadence="antecedent">ate</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="3">And trouble deaf heaven with my bootless cr<rhyme scheme="A" type="perfect" cadence="consequent">ies</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="4">And look upon myself, and curse my f<rhyme scheme="B" type="perfect" cadence="consequent">ate</rhyme>;</line>
		</quatrain>
		<quatrain number="2">
			<line number="1">Wishing me like to one more rich in h<rhyme scheme="C" type="perfect" cadence="antecedent">ope</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="2">Featur'd like him, like him with friends poss<rhyme scheme="D" type="near" cadence="antecedent">ess'd</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="3">Desiring this man's art, and that man's sc<rhyme scheme="C" type="perfect" cadence="consequent">ope</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="4">With what I most enjoy contented l<rhyme scheme="D" type="near" cadence="consequent">east</rhyme>;</line>
		</quatrain>
		<quatrain number="3">
			<line number="1">Yet in these thoughts my self almost desp<rhyme scheme="E" type="perfect" cadence="antecedent">ising</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="2">Haply I think on thee,-- and then my st<rhyme scheme="F" type="perfect" cadence="antecedent">ate</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="3">Like to the lark at break of day ar<rhyme scheme="E" type="perfect" cadence="consequent">ising</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="4">From sullen earth, sings hymns at heaven's g<rhyme scheme="F" type="perfect" cadence="consequent">ate</rhyme>;</line>
		</quatrain>
		<couplet>
			<line number="1">For thy sweet love remember'd such wealth br<rhyme scheme="G" type="perfect" cadence="antecedent">ings</rhyme>,</line>
			<line number="2">That then I scorn to change my state with k<rhyme scheme="G" type="perfect" cadence="consequent">ings</rhyme>.</line>
		</couplet>
		<author>
			<name>William Shakespeare</name>
			<date>(1564-1616)</date>
		</author>
	</sonnet>
</document>
